nearly every realm of American life, and is further perpetuated by failures to address the compounding effects of generations of disinvestment. Police violence, mass incarceration of Black people, employment and housing discrimination, economic deprivation, and gross inequities in health care combine to deeply embed racial inequality in American society and economy. Updated to include the most recent evidence, including contemporary research on the racially disparate effects of the Covid-19 pandemic, this edition of Whitewashing Race analyzes the consequential and ongoing legacy of ";disaccumulation"; for Black communities and lives. While some progress has been made, the authors argue that real racial justice can be achieved only if we actively attack and undo pervasive structural racism and its legacies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican AmericansxCivil rights. 0aRacismzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Race & Ethnic Relations.2bisacsh1 aCarnoy, Martin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCurrie, Elliott, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aOppenheimer, David B., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520394605?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97805203946054